        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 6:25PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 13 miles northwest of Shepherd to near
Huntley, or extending from 20 miles north of Billings to 13 miles
east of Billings, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ballantine, Worden, Huntley and Pompeys Pillar. This does not
include the city of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
